<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p><p>ABOUT THE AUTHOR</p>
</p><p>For twenty-five years, HAROLD J. ROTHWAX has been a judge on the New York State Supreme Court. He has also been a senior trial attorney for the Criminal Defense Division of the Legal Aid Society, a vice chairperson of the New York Civil Liberties Union, and a lecturer at Columbia Law School for the past twenty-five years, and he was a Guggenheim Fellow at the Yale Law School in 1984. He is a recipient of the New York State Bar Association Award for Outstanding Achievements in the field of Criminal Law Education. He lives in New York City with his wife, Yona. They have two children. <br>
</p>
