<html><head><title>The Beardstown Ladies' Stitch-in-Time Guide to Growing Your Nest Egg. </title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
</tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> B<font size=-1>EARDSTOWN</font> L<font size=-1>ADIES'</font> S<font size=-1>TITCH-IN-</font>T<font size=-1>IME</font> G<font size=-1>UIDE</font> <font size=-1>TO</font> G<font size=-1>ROWING</font> Y<font size=-1>OUR</font> N<font size=-1>EST</font> E<font size=-1>GG</font>. <br></h2>
<p>By Ian Knight.<br>
<br>
<i>Hyperion; 255 pages; $19.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3bt29.html">Biography</a><br>
<p><b>Jacket Copy</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>THE BEARDSTOWN LADIES' STITCH-IN-TIME GUIDE TO GROWING YOUR NEST EGG
</p><p>STEP-BY-STEP PLANNING FORA COMFORTABLE FINANCIAL FUTURE
</p><p>The Beardstown Ladies' Investment Club with Robin Dellabough
</p><p>"The Beardstown Ladies have proven once again that a disciplined approach to picking stocks pays off in the long run." - Peter Lynch
</p><p>On the heels of their instant national bestseller, The Beardstown Ladies' Common-Sense Investment Guide, the same savvy ladies who have beaten the market for over a decade now turn their sights toward retirement in a practical, friendly planning guide to the golden years. Famous for their 23.4% average annual returns that have amazed even the Wall Street community, these sixteen ladies explain how you, too, can guarantee yourself a financially secure retirement. From the basics of financial planning and goal-setting to the nuts and bolts of saving strategies and investment tactics, the Beardstown Ladies take you by the hand and guide you through it all. You'll learn how to create your own personalized investment portfolio and more, including the straight facts on 401Ks and pension plans; how much insurance you should have; what to expect from Social Security and Medicare; choosing the right combination of savings, investments, and money markets; plus everything you need to know about mutual funds, CDs, Treasury bills, stocks, and bonds.
</p><p>Including worksheets, charts, graphs, and a list of the "Do's and Don'ts" of retirement planning, The Beardstown Ladies' Stitch-in-Time Guide to Growing Your Nest Egg is for anyone who would like to live out his or her golden years in comfort - just like The Beardstown Ladies! <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
