<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>S<font size=-1>TEINWAY</font> &amp; S<font size=-1>ONS</font><br></h2>
<p>By Richard Lieberman.<br>
<i>374 pages</i>;<i> Yale University Press</i>; <i>$35</i> and <i>&#163;23.50</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb21.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>Richard K. Lieberman is professor of history at LaGuardian Community College of the City University of New York and director of the LaGuardia and Wagner Archives, which house the Steinway collection. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
