<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> W<font size=-1>ORLD</font> T<font size=-1>HE</font> W<font size=-1>ORLD</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Norman Lewis. <br>
<i>Jonathan Cape; 240 pages; &#163;18.99.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="8jb229.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Norman Lewis was born in London. He has written thirteen novels and eleven
non-fiction works. A Dragon Apparent and Golden Earth are considered
classics of travel literature, and Naples '44 has been described as one of the ten
outstanding books about the Second World War. He relaxes by his travels to
off-beat parts of the world, which he prefers to be as remote as possible;
otherwise he lives with his family in introspective, almost monastic calm in the
depths of Essex.
