<h2>D<font size=-1>ESERT</font> P<font size=-1>LACES</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Robyn Davidson. <br>
<i> Viking; 288 pages; &#163;18 and $23.95.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="8jb246.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Robyn Davidson was born in Queensland and now lives in London. Tracks, an
account of her 1,700-mile journey across Australia with camels, won the 1980
Thomas Cook Travel Book Award. She is also the author of the novel
Ancestors, which was short-listed for the Premier's Award, and of a collection
of essays, Travelling Light.
