<html><head><title>Lewis Carroll</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl268.jpg"><img src="cs268.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>L<font size=-1>EWIS</font> C<font size=-1>ARROLL:<br></font> <font size=-1>A</font> P<font size=-1>ORTRAIT</font> <font size=-1>WITH</font> B<font size=-1>ACKGROUND</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Donald Thomas. <br>
<i>John Murray; 404 pages; &#163;25</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="9jb268.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Donald Thomas was born in Somerset, and educated at Queen's College,
Taunton, and Balliol College, Oxford. His poems Points of Contact won the
Eric Gregory Award and his biography Robert Browning was runner-up for the
Whitbread Award.
<p>His fiction has brought the Stuarts to the throne of Virginia in Prince Charlie's Bluff and blackmail with murder to Victorian Oxford in Belladonna: A Lewis Carroll Nightmare. Recent novels include his 1940s thriller Dancing in the Dark, The Arrest of Scotland Yard and The Raising of Lizzy Meek, based on the miracles attributed to Father Ignatius of Capel-y-ffin.</p>
<p>His documentary crime includes Hanged in Error and Dead Giveaway, an account of the forensic detection of Cardiff's 'Body in the Carpet' murder.</p>
<p>Since 1985 he has held a personal chair in the University ofWales. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?842655600,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
