<html><head><title>People, Performance and Pay</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>

</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>P<font size=-1>EOPLE</font>, P<font size=-1>ERFORMANCE</font> <font size=-1>AND</font> P<font size=-1>AY</font><br></h2>
<p>By Thomas Flannery, David Hofrichter and Paul Platten.<br>
<i>Free Press; 269 pages; $27</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="4jb92.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>THOMAS P. FLANNERY, Vice President and Managing Director of The Hay Group, is a recognized leader in helping organizations dramatically improve performance. He is the author of The Hay Guide to Executive Compensation in Health Care and holds a Ph.D. from Northwestern University. He currently lives in Singapore. DAVID A. HOFRICHTER, an expert in compensation, leadership, and the role both play in change management, is the Managing Director of Hay's Global Accounts, Client Relationship Development program. A Vice President of Hay, he is responsible for the firm's midwest offices. He earned a Ph.D. from Duquesne University and lives in Chicago. PAUL E. PLATTEN, a Vice President and General Manager of The Hay Group's Boston office, has done extensive work in executive compensation and is a frequent speaker on the subject of compensation and the changing organization. He received a Ph.D. from New York University and lives in Boston. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?826927200,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
