<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> M<font size=-1>ISSIONARY</font> <font size=-1>AND</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> L<font size=-1>IBERTINE</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Ian Buruma. <br>
<i>Faber; 336 pages; &#163;16</i>.<i>99</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="7jb206.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Ian Baruma was educated in Holland and Japan, and has spend many years in
Asia, which he has written about in books such as God's Dust and A Japanese
Mirror. He has also written a novel, Playing the Game, a fictional biography of
K.S. Ranjitsinhji, the Indian prince who played cricket for the MCC in
Edwardian Britain. The Wages of Guilt, an exploration of how Germany and
Japan have come to terms with their aggressive past, was published in 1994. Ian
Baruma lives in London.
