<html><head><title>Splash!</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl227.jpg"><img src="cs227.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>S<font size=-1>PLASH</font>!:<br> G<font size=-1>REAT</font> W<font size=-1>RITING</font> <font size=-1>ABOUT</font> S<font size=-1>WIMMING</font>.<br></h2>
<p> Edited by Laurel Blossom. <br>
<i>Ecco Press; 254 pages; &#163;26</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="8jb227.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Laurel Blossom is the author of three volumes of poetry: Any Minute, What's
Wrong, and The Papers Said. She has received grants from the National
Endowment for the Arts, the New York Foundation for the Arts, and the Ohio
Arts Council. She is cofounder of The Writers Community, a workshop and
residency program and now part of the National Writer's Voice Project of the
YMCA.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
</td></tr></table></body></html>
