<html><head><title>Braving the Elements</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl210.jpg"><img src="cs210.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>B<font size=-1>RAVING</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> E<font size=-1>LEMENTS:<br></font> T<font size=-1>HE</font> S<font size=-1>TORMY</font> H<font size=-1>ISTORY</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> A<font size=-1>MERICAN</font> W<font size=-1>EATHER</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By David Laskin. <br>
<i>Doubleday; 352 pages; $23.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="7jb210.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
David Laskin is the author of a number of nonfiction books, including A
Common Life: Four Generations of American Literary Friendship and The
Reading Group Book. A lifelong weather enthusiast, Laskin has published
articles about the environment, travel, and family issues in numerous
publications. He recently moved to the not-as-rainy-as-everyone-thinks climes
of Seattle, Washington.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?834793200,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
