<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> E<font size=-1>ND</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> S<font size=-1>CIENCE</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By John Horgan. <br>
<i>Addison-Wesley; 309 pages; $24.00.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="8jb255.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
John Horgan is a senior writer at Scientific American. His articles have
appeared in The New York Times Book Review,. The New Republic, Discover,
New Scientist, Science, and Omni. He lives in New York state's Hudson Valley
with his wife and their two children.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
