<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> Q<font size=-1>UEEN:<br></font> A B<font size=-1>IOGRAPHY</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> E<font size=-1>LIZABETH</font> II.<br></h2>
<p> By Ben Pimlott. <br>
<i>HarperCollins; 651 pages; &#163;20</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11jb336.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Ben Pimlott is Professor of Politics and Contemporary History at Birkbeck College, University of
London. He is the author of Labour and the Left in the 1930s (1977), Hugh Dalton (1985), which won
the Whitbread Prize, Harold Wilson (1992), and a collection of essays, Frustrate Their Knavish Tricks
(1994). He is a Fellow of the British Academy.
