<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> B<font size=-1>USINESS</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> E<font size=-1>CONOMICS</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By John Kay. <br>
<i>OUP; 216 pages; &#163;17.99</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11jb347.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
John Kay is Visiting Professor of Economics at the London Business School and Chairman of London
Economics, a leading consultancy whose clients include many blue-chip companies. He is also the
director of several public companies, and has been adviser and consultant to both parliamentary select
committees and governments. The author of numerous books including Foundations of Corporate
Success (OUP, 1993) and The British Tax System (OUP, 1990), he broadcasts regularly on business
and economic affairs.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
