<h2>B<font size=-1>ORN</font> <font size=-1>TO</font> R<font size=-1>EBEL</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Frank Sulloway<br>
<i>Little, Brown; 653 pages; &#163;20. Pantheon; $30.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="12jb358.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Frank 1. Sulloway is a Research Scholar at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. The findings published in Bom to Rebel, the product of over twenty years' research, have attracted high-profile media attention in America, and have been encouraged by leading scientists in the fields of biology, developmental psychology and human behaviour.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
