</p><br>
<a href="8jb231.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
SANDRA MACKEY has written on the culture and politics of the Middle East
for such periodicals as the Los Angeles Times, the Wall Street Journal, the
Christian Science Monitor, and the Chicago Tribune. Appearing as a guest
expert on Nightline, ABC News with Peter Jennings, and National Public
Radio, she also served as a Gulf War commentaror for CNN. She is the author
of three previous acclaimed books: The Saadis: Inside the Desert Kingdom,
Lebanon: Death of a Nation, and Passion and Politics: The Turbulent World of
the Arabs. She lives in Atlanta.
