<html><head><title>Home Grown Fantasy.</title></head>
<body background="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl250.jpg"><img src="cs250.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>H<font size=-1>OME</font> G<font size=-1>ROWN</font> F<font size=-1>ANTASY</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Zion Train. <br>
<i>China Records</i>.<br>
</p><br>
<p><b>Jacket Copy</p></b>
Welcome to the Wibbly Wobbly World of Zion Train ...
<p>By clicking on different parts of the leaf you'll be propelled into one of the many zones; the world of sound, the Zion Train tree, the natural world &amp; the never ending fact well. From there it's a wondrous exploration through the innumerable paths of one of the most astoundingly elaborate &amp; enigmatic CD- Roms ever made.</p>
<p>Among the packed selection of features are a fully remixable track unique to the CD-ROM, phonetic interview with the band conducted by Jamie Reid (situationist and Sex Pistols' graphic artist), 3 of Zion Train's videos, the history of radio, the tree house gallery, a step by step guide to making your own records and hundreds of bizarre &amp; interesting facts.</p>
<p>PLUS, separately on the disc is a giveaway section full of images, sound samples, animations and information including the mysterious primate primer and the WobblyNET html pages. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.europe.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
