<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Carl Bernstein won the Pulitzer Prize for his coverage of the Watergate scandal
for the Washington Post. His book on the subject. All the President's Men,
written with Bob Woodward, became an international bestseller and was
followed by The Final Days He lives and works in New York City.
<p>Marco Politi, one of Italy s premier journalists, has covered the papacy for the past twenty years and is Vatican corespondent for La Repubblica. He was also a Moscow correspondent for five years. He lives in Rome. </p>
