<html><head><title>The Gorbachev Factor. By Archie Brown.  oup; 406 pages; &#163;19.99 and $30</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl346.jpg"><img src="cs346.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> G<font size=-1>ORBACHEV</font> F<font size=-1>ACTOR</font>. By Archie Brown.  <font size=-1>OUP; </font><i>406 pages; &#163;19.99 and $30</i><br></h2>
<p><i>406 pages; &#163;19.99 and $30</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11jb346.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Archie Brown is Professor of Politics at the University of Oxford and Sub-Warden of St
Antony's College where he has been a Fellow since 1971. Earlier he studied at the London
School of Economics and Political Science and taught at Glasgow University. A frequent
traveller to both Russia and the United States, he has held visiting professorships at Yale,
Columbia, and the University of Texas at Austin, as well as at the European business school,
INSEAD, in Fontainebleau He was elected a Fellow of the British Academy in 1991
<p>Professor Brown is the author of numerous publications on Soviet and Russian politics. His more recent works (as editor and major contributor) include The Cambridge Encyclopedia of Russia and the Former Soviet Union (Cambridge and New York, 1994), New Thinking in Soviet Politics (London and New York, 1992), The Soviet Union: A Biographical Dictionary (London, 1990, and New York, 1991), and Political Leadership in the Soviet Union (London and Bloomington, Indiana, 1989). </p>
