<html><head><title>Spokesmen for the Despised.</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl356.jpg"><img src="cs356.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td><h2>J<font size=-1>WAHARLAL</font> N<font size=-1>EHRU</font>. <br></h2><p>By B.R. Nanda <br><i>OUP; 312 pages; &#163;16.99</i><br>
</p><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11jb356.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
B.R. Nanda is Chief Editor, Collected Works of Govind Ballabh Pant
Project and was formerly Founder-Director of the Nehru Memorial
Museum and Library. He is the author of a number of distinguished
political biographies including Mahatma Gandhi: A Biography and The
Nehrus: Motilal and Jawaharlal.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?848102400,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
