<i>University of Michigan Press; 379 pages; $29.95 and &#163;19.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="10jb306.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
Since graduating in Chinese Studies from Oxford, James Miles has worked as a
journalist in China and Hong Kong. After eight years in Beijing, mainly with
the BBC, he wrote this book while on a Fellowship at the University of
Michigan. He is now back in the Far East as the BBC's Hong Kong
Correspondent.
