<html><head><title>A History of Europe.</title></head>
<body background="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl339.jpg"><img src="cs339.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>A H<font size=-1>ISTORY OF</font> E<font size=-1>UROPE</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By J.M. Roberts. <br>
<i>Helicon; 640 pages; &#163;25.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11bt339.html">Biography</a>
<p><b>Jacket Copy</p></b>
The history of the world has been influenced in a profound way by the history
of Europe. The development and universal spread of 'western values' has
brought prosperity, as well as destruction, to all it touches. How is it that the
small continent of Europe, with its rich multiplicity of cultures and traditions,
has had this farreaching effect? Writing in his appealing story-telling style, J M
Roberts untangles the themes and values which still propel us today. Antiquity,
the age of Christendom, the Middle Ages, early modern history and the old
European order are exammed in turn. The turbulent twentieth century is given
proportionally a more detailed treatment.
<p>Narrative history from a master of the genre, A History of Europe brings into focus not only what Europeans have done, but what they have thought of themselves. Although knowing the past does not confer an ability to predict the future (no apocalyptic predictions for the millennium are made), the reader of J M Roberts' A History of Europe will nonetheless be equipped with both a broad and a deep understanding of the European peoples' history. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.europe.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?848102400,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.europe.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
</td></tr></table></body></html>
