<h2>W<font size=-1>ORLD</font> H<font size=-1>ISTORY</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Hugh Thomas. <br>
<i>HarperCollins; 764 pages; $35</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="11jb335.html">Jacket Copy</a>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
HUGH THOMAS is a historian living in London. His principal work has been in the world of
Spanish studies: for example, The Spanish Civil War (1961, revised edition 1977), Cuba: The
Pursuit of Freedom (1971) and Conquest: Montezuma, Cortes and the Fall of Old Mexico
(1993). He has, however, also published History of the World (1980), a history of the causes of
the Cold War--Armed Truce (1986)--a biography of John Strachey (1973) and some polemical
literature for example, Europe: The Radical Challenge (1973)--as well as several novels. Hugh
Thomas was chairman of the Centre for Policy Studies from 1979-1989, was given a peerage
as Lord Thomas of Swynnerton in 1981, and was King Juan Carlos I professor at New York
University 1991-1996.
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a>
